    <title>Concepts</title>
    <para>The concepts covered in this section describe the components of Cloud Networks.</para>
    <?dbhtml stop-chunking?>
    <!-- Network -->
    <section xml:id="conceptNetwork">
        <title>Network</title>
        <para>A network is an isolated virtual layer-2 broadcast domain that is typically reserved for the tenant who created
            it . Tenants can create multiple networks until the thresholds per-tenant quota is reached. This threshold is
            currently set to 10 networks per region. </para>
        <para>In the Networking API v2.0, the network is the main entity. Ports and subnets are always associated with a
            network.</para>
